Claims Claims: 1. Apparatus having mutually orthogonal x, y, and z axes, wherein the z axis runs vertically, for machining a work piece using a tool bit having a lengthwise axis oriented along the z axis which comprises: (a) a machine tool comprising a work table, for holding a work piece; a spindle, having a lower end portion for directly or indirectly holding and rotating about the z axis the shank of an end mill tool bit, the spindle configured for moving said tool bit in the z axis direction; one or more slides, connected directly or indirectly to the spindle, for moving the spindle and said tool bit in one or both of the x-axis direction and y-axis direction; wherein said one or more slides are located at an elevation higher than the elevation of said lower end portion of the spindle; and, (b) a fluid handling system for channeling and processing liquid coolant and air, comprising an enclosure, comprised of side walls, a floor, and one or more access doors in a side wall; one or more shields, each having a horizontal portion that partitions within the apparatus an upper region which is a space at a higher elevation than the spindle lower end portion from a lower region which is a space at a lower elevation than the spindle lower end portion; and, at least one air mover for flowing air from said upper region to said lower region; 

 a coolant handling system for flowing coolant from said lower region to vicinity of said spindle lower end portion. 2. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein the horizontal portion of at least one of said shields is movable in the x or y axis direction in coordination with the x or y axis movement of the spindle. 3. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein the horizontal portion of said at least one shield is fastened to either side walls of the enclosure or to the spindle, the shield comprised of semi-rigid sheet. 4. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein the horizontal portion of said at least one shield is fastened to both to the side walls of the enclosure and to the spindle, the shield made of flexible or elastic sheet that enables spindle movement relative to the side walls of the enclosure. 5. The apparatus of claim 2 wherein said at least one shield is made of flexible sheet which runs either as a continuous loop around a multiplicity of spaced apart roller pairs or between reels that are horizontally spaced apart as a reel pair. 6. The apparatus of claim 5 wherein each of the rollers of a roller pair or each of the reels of a reel pair of said at least one shield is located in close proximity to a side wall of the enclosure, so there is a slot-like opening space between each roller or reel and its respective close proximity side wall for flow of air from said upper region to said lower region. 7. The apparatus of claim 5 comprising a first shield having a horizontal portion movable to and fro along one of the x-axis or y-axis; and a second shield made of flexible sheet and having a horizontal portion movable to and fro along a horizontal axis that is at right angles to movement direction of the horizontal portion of the first shield, wherein the horizontal portions of the two shields are in close vertical proximity to each other. 8. The apparatus of claim 7 wherein the first shield comprises a continuous loop of sheet material running around a plurality of rollers, the loop having a lower portion which comprises said horizontal portion of the first shield and the loop having an upper horizontal portion located in said upper region at an elevation which is above the elevation of said slides. 9. The apparatus of claim 8 wherein the second shield comprises sheet having a horizontal portion running between rollers spaced apart along the sheet path and then upwardly from each said roller to a reel about which the sheet furls and unfurls when the spindle moves horizontally. 10. The apparatus of claim 1 further comprising apparatus for separating coolant carried by air, in flow communication with an outflow port of said enclosure located at said lower region, wherein air flows from the apparatus for separating directly or indirectly to said upper region. 11. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein the shield is spaced apart from the side walls of the enclosure location to define at least two slot like spaces for airflow from said upper region to said lower region; further comprising at least one bypass duct, for carrying further air from the upper region to the lower region . 12. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein said enclosure sidewalls extend upwardly to enclose said upper region of the apparatus; further comprising an enclosure roof connecting the sidewalls and covering said upper region, the roof having a plurality of openings for flow of air into the upper region from outside the apparatus. 13. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein the work table is horizontally fixed during machining. 14. Apparatus having mutually orthogonal x, y, and z axes, wherein the z axis runs vertically, for machining a work piece using a tool bit having a lengthwise axis oriented along the z axis which comprises: (a) a machine tool comprising a work table, for holding a work piece; a spindle, having a lower end portion for directly or indirectly holding and rotating about the z axis the shank of an end mill tool bit, the spindle configured for moving said tool bit in the z axis direction; 

 one or more slides, connected directly or indirectly to the spindle, for moving the spindle and said tool bit in one or both of the x-axis direction and y-axis direction; wherein said one or more slides are located at an elevation higher than the elevation of said lower end portion of the spindle; and, a fluid handling system for channeling and processing liquid coolant and air, comprising an enclosure, comprised of side walls, a floor, and one or more access doors in a side wall; at least two shields, each made of flexible sheet and having a horizontal portion, the shields cooperatively partitioning the apparatus into an upper region which is a space at a higher elevation than the spindle lower end portion from a lower region which is a space at a lower elevation than the spindle lower end portion; the at least two shields comprising a first shield having a horizontal portion movable to and fro along one of the x-axis or y-axis; and a second shield having a horizontal portion movable to and fro along a horizontal axis that is at right angles to movement direction of the horizontal portion of the first shield; wherein the horizontal portions of the two shields are in close vertical proximity to each other; wherein each of the two shields run either as a continuous loop around a multiplicity of spaced apart roller pairs or between reels that are horizontally spaced apart as a reel pair; wherein each of the rollers of a roller pair and each of the reels of a reel pair of said shields are located in close proximity to a side wall of the enclosure, so there is a slot-like opening space between each roller or reel and its respective close proximity side wall for flow of air from said upper region to said lower region; at least one air mover for flowing air from said upper region to said lower region; and, a coolant handling system for flowing coolant from said lower region to vicinity of said spindle lower end portion. 15. The apparatus of claim 14 wherein the first shield comprises a continuous loop of sheet material running around a plurality of rollers, the loop having a lower portion which comprises said horizontal portion of the first shield and the loop having an upper portion located in said upper region and above the elevation of said slides; and wherein the second shield comprises sheet having a horizontal portion running between rollers spaced apart along the sheet path, and then upwardly from each said roller to a reel about which the sheet furls and unfurls when the spindle moves horizontally. 16. The apparatus of claim 1 further comprising: an access door in a sidewall of the enclosure, openable and closeable to enable a tool tray within the lower region of the enclosure to be positioned on or removed from a support surface within the enclosure; a horizontal support surface for holding a tool tray, positioned within the lower region of the enclosure in proximity to said access door; a housing for said tool tray, shaped for covering a tool tray set upon said support surface, the housing having a movable cover which prevents coolant or air within the lower region from substantially contacting the support surface and any tool tray resting thereon when the access door is open. 17. The apparatus of claim 16 wherein the movable cover is hinged to the rest of the housing. 18. The apparatus of claim 17 further comprising: a tool tray movably mounted on said work table, the tray having surface for holding a multiplicity of tool assemblies, each tool assembly comprising an adapter and a milling tool bit. 19. The apparatus of claim 16 wherein the support surface is adjacent the work table. 20. A method of machining workpieces which comprises: 

 (a) providing an apparatus of claim 16, wherein a tool tray having a multiplicity of assemblies is positioned on the support surface; (b) opening the movable cover of the housing to expose the multiplicity of tool assemblies, each assembly comprising a tool bit; (c) engaging at one or more tool assemblies serially with the lower end portion of the spindle; (d) closing the cover of the housing; (e) machining the work piece using a tool assembly engaged with the spindle while flowing coolant to the vicinity of the lower portion of the spindle and while flowing air from the upper region to the lower region, wherein the cover of the housing protects the tool tray on the support surface; and, (f) during the machining step, opening the access door in the side of the enclosure and removing the tool tray from the support surface; optionally positioning a second too tray having a second multiplicity of tool assemblies on the support surface; and closing the access door.
